requirements:
Small but busy law firm seeks a highly motivated law school student to join our team. This is for an in-office position with a flexible schedule, however some remote work is possible. Prefer a student that is at least in their second semester of law school and is not on academic probation for any reason. Ability to speak multi languages a plus but not a requirement. Need to have a great attitude and work well with others as you will be directly assisting two attorneys.

This is a great opportunity to learn and grow with our firm. You will be in the middle of the action, but will also perform some administrative tasks, which will likewise provide you with experience in office management.

Among the tasks you will be performing includes but is not limited to:

· Legal Research;

· Drafting Legal Memorandum;

· Drafting Legal Complaints;

· Drafting Demand Letters, including 93A

· Legal Filings;

· Legal Analysis;

· Develop course of actions and remedies with Attorneys;

· Document reviewing and/or proofreading;

· Assist in Court Proceedings;

· Assist in Court Preparation;

· Assist in Client Intake and Consultations

· Assist with Phone;

· Assist with Emails;

· Mail Preparation;

· Scanning;

· Assist with office Filings;

· And more.

In doing these tasks, you will gain experience in several areas of law, including, but not limited to, Family Law, Immigration, Contract Law, Personal Injury, Landlord/Tenant Law, Land Disputes, Civil Litigation, Criminal Law, Business Law, Discrimination Law, Employment Law, and more.

If you are eager to learn and get hands on experience then please send in a cover letter, your resume, as well as a writing sample.

Job Types: Part-time, Internship

Pay: $10.00 per year

Schedule:
• Day shift

Work Location:
• One location

Hours per week:
• 10-19

Company's website:
• aroldlawfirm.com

